## What SafeEat Is

SafeEat is a QR-powered safe-return CRM for independent UK food businesses — cafés, restaurants, takeaways, and market stalls. It turns the allergen compliance obligation every food business already has into a customer retention engine that drives repeat visits from the most loyal, highest-spending customer segment in hospitality: food-allergic diners.

---

## The Problem It Solves

Two problems, currently solved by two separate product categories that don't talk to each other:

**Problem 1 — Compliance:** UK food businesses must provide allergen information for non-prepacked food (Food Information Regulations 2014). The FSA's March 2025 guidance now sets an expectation that this information be provided in writing, not just verbally. Owen's Law (mandatory written allergen labelling) is progressing toward legislation, with the FSA evaluating the guidance's uptake from spring 2026. Most small businesses currently handle this with paper matrices, verbal "just ask staff" signage, or nothing at all. Compliance rates have dropped from 74% to 53% (Serve Legal, 2025). Prosecutions are accelerating — fines ranging from £1,920 to £43,816 for independent businesses in 2025–2026 alone.

**Problem 2 — Retention:** Food-allergic customers are twice as loyal as non-allergic customers, less price-sensitive, bring groups of 3–4 people per visit, and actively recommend venues they trust (FSA research, FARE/EveryBite data, McKinsey). But 42–60% avoid eating out entirely because they don't feel safe. When they do find a safe venue, nobody captures them — no profile, no follow-up, no "come back" mechanism. Existing allergen tools (Allergen Checker, Menu Guide, Allergy Menu) display compliance information and stop. Existing loyalty tools (Embargo, Stamp Me, Loyalzoo) capture visit behaviour but know nothing about dietary needs. Nobody connects the two.

---

## What SafeEat Does

SafeEat is the bridge. One product. Four promises:

1. **Save my profile once.** Customer selects their allergens from the 14 UK-regulated list. Profile saved. Never re-entered.
2. **Show me what's safe now.** Filtered menu shows only safe dishes. Green "safe for you" tags. Unsafe dishes hidden.
3. **Remember me next time.** Profile persists across visits. Customer scans the same QR or opens their saved link — menu loads with their profile, no friction.
4. **Prove the menu is current.** Weekly verification by venue owner. "Last verified" badge visible to customers. Goes amber after 14 days, suppresses personalised claims after 28 days.

