## The 90-Second Customer Journey

### Visit 1: First Scan

1. Customer sees QR code on menu, counter, receipt, or window sticker
2. Scans with phone camera — no app download, opens as PWA in browser
3. Branded digital menu loads for that specific venue
4. Banner: "Have allergies? Tap to filter your menu"
5. Customer selects allergens (milk, nuts, gluten, etc.) — one tap each
6. Menu instantly filters to safe dishes only, each with green "Safe for you" tag
7. Prompt: "Save your profile so [Venue Name] can remember you next time?"
   - Explicit GDPR Article 9 consent: two separate opt-ins
   - Opt-in 1: Save dietary profile (for filtering on return visits)
   - Opt-in 2: Receive notifications about new safe dishes (marketing)
   - "No thanks" still shows filtered menu for this session — no profile saved
8. Customer saves profile → gets bookmark/home-screen prompt via PWA manifest
9. No account creation, no password, no app download

### Between Visits: The Safe Return Loop

10. Venue owner adds or changes a dish/ingredient
11. System cross-references against saved customer profiles
12. Matching customers receive notification: "[Venue Name] just added a new nut-free brownie. Your usual flat white is still safe too."
13. Notification includes one-tap link back to their personalised safe menu

### Visit 2+: The Return

14. Customer returns, scans QR or opens saved link
15. Menu loads instantly with their saved allergen profile — no re-entering. Service worker caches menu for instant load even on poor signal.
16. "Welcome back" header, "Last verified [date]" badge
17. Customer orders with confidence. Venue has retained a high-value customer without a single discount or stamp card.

### Venue Side: Weekly Verification

18. Every Monday 8am: push/email to venue owner — "Confirm your menu is still accurate"
19. Owner taps confirm (no changes) or updates affected dishes
20. "Last verified" badge updates on customer-facing menu
21. If no verification for 14 days: badge turns amber, customer sees "Menu not recently verified — please check with staff"
22. If no verification for 28 days: personalised "safe for you" claims suppressed, menu reverts to standard allergen matrix only

