## Security Implementation (Autaimate Standard v2 — All 8 Layers)

### Layer 1: Input Validation & Sanitisation
- `utils/validation.ts` — validateInput() for email, number, text, currency, allergen selection
- DOMPurify on all user-submitted text (dish names, descriptions, ingredient names)
- All validation patterns from Build Standard Layer 1 applied

### Layer 2: CSRF Protection
- `utils/csrf.ts` — CSRF tokens on all POST/PUT/DELETE operations
- Venue dashboard dish creation, ingredient updates, verification confirmations all CSRF-protected
- Customer profile save uses CSRF token

### Layer 3: Session Management & Timeout
- `hooks/useSessionTimeout.ts` — 15-minute absolute, 10-minute idle for venue owner dashboard
- Customer-facing PWA has no session (profile is stateless, keyed to hashed identifier)

### Layer 4: Secure API Calls
- `hooks/useFetch.ts` — SSRF protection (relative URLs only), credentials: include, Sentry error capture
- No API keys in client code — all sensitive calls through Cloudflare Workers

### Layer 5: Error Tracking with Sentry
- `utils/errorTracking.ts` — Sentry init with PII stripping, replay masking
- Authorization and CSRF headers stripped from Sentry events
- Allergen data NEVER sent to Sentry

### Layer 6: Rate Limiting via Upstash
- Public endpoints (QR scan/menu fetch): 30 requests per 60 seconds per IP
- Profile save: 5 requests per 60 seconds per IP
- Notification send (venue): 100 per hour per venue
- Dashboard auth endpoints: 10 per 60 seconds per IP

### Layer 7: Security Headers (Railway/Caddy)
- X-Frame-Options: DENY
- X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
- X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
- Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
- Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
- Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://api.safeeat.co.uk https://sentry.io; frame-ancestors 'none'
- Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

### Layer 8: Environment Variables
- All secrets in Railway/Workers environment variables
- .env.example committed, .env.local in .gitignore
- VITE_ prefix for client-safe variables only
- Database URL, Stripe secret key, Clerk secret key — backend only, never prefixed

