## Neon PostgreSQL Security (Addendum H2 Pattern)

### Row-Level Security (RLS)
Every table containing venue data MUST have RLS enabled:

```sql
ALTER TABLE dishes ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY dishes_own_venue ON dishes
  FOR ALL
  USING (venue_id::text = current_setting('app.current_venue_id', true))
  WITH CHECK (venue_id::text = current_setting('app.current_venue_id', true));
```

RLS applied to: dishes, ingredients, dish_ingredients, customer_venues, verification_log, notification_log.

### pgcrypto Encryption at Rest
Customer allergen profiles are UK GDPR Article 9 special-category data. Encrypted using pgcrypto:

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "pgcrypto";

-- Encrypt allergen data on insert
INSERT INTO customer_profiles (hashed_identifier, contact_encrypted, allergens_encrypted)
VALUES (
  $1,
  encrypt_value($2, current_setting('app.encryption_key')),
  encrypt_value($3, current_setting('app.encryption_key'))
);

-- Decrypt for allergen filtering
SELECT decrypt_value(allergens_encrypted, current_setting('app.encryption_key')) as allergens
FROM customer_profiles WHERE hashed_identifier = $1;
```

### Append-Only Audit Log
All consent changes, profile deletions, and verification events logged:

```sql
CREATE TABLE audit_log (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  venue_id uuid,
  actor_type text NOT NULL,
  action text NOT NULL,
  metadata jsonb,
  ip_hash text,
  created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE ON audit_log FROM app_role;
```

