## Consent Flow (UK GDPR Article 9)

### Legal Basis
- **Processing allergen data:** Explicit consent — Article 9(2)(a)
- **Sending notifications:** Consent — Article 6(1)(a) + PECR regulation 22

### In-Product Consent Screen

```
Save your dietary needs

[Venue Name] will store which allergens you've selected so we can:
✓ Show you only safe dishes when you visit
✓ Remember your needs for next time

Your allergy information is encrypted and never shared.

[Save my profile]    [No thanks, just show me today's menu]

─────────────────────

☐ Also let [Venue Name] message me when they add
  new dishes safe for me (you can unsubscribe anytime)
```

### Consent Rules
- Two separate consents — never bundled
- "No thanks" still shows filtered menu for current session
- Profile consent can exist without marketing consent
- One-tap profile deletion: immediate, irreversible, confirmed via email/SMS
- Consent record stored in audit_log: timestamp, version, IP hash, scope
- Auto-delete profiles inactive for 18 months (scheduled worker)

